<|startoftext|>Wow! This place is awesome! My friend and I went there for lunch last Sunday. It's just about the size of your average pub on South Street. There is a patio here that is the perfect cooler for the warmer months. The service was great and the food was hot and fresh. We also ordered a side of garlic bread with chicken. The garlic bread was a bit too hot for me personally but if you are a garlic bread lover definitely order a dip that is warm to touch. The chicken was great and cooked well. My friend said that the chicken was a bit overcooked but other than being cooked it was good.\n\nWe got the chicken pizza and were pretty well taken care of and it was tasty. My friend and I both ordered the salad and were also just taken care of and the dressing was great.\n\nIt's a great place to stop if you are hungry and craving pub food here!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>I have been a fan of this place since the opening years.  The service is pretty good here.  I've had a few things on the menu, which is hard to mess up at a Pub.  Usually I get the burger, which is about $8-9.  My friend and I both get the Cajun shrimp.  It's kind of hard to choose what combination of fries, onion rings, and coleslaw we want on our fries.   There's some options here, but I'm probably never going back again.  I can imagine that you can just buy a packet in bulk from the freezer and freeze it for later.  You can't do that at this place, tho.  The burgers really aren't all that good, which makes sense as the Cajun is an immigrant burger joint.  \n\nThey're only open on Sunday, which is also the day before the NFL is usually when they're doing well.  I guess this is a bar that people like to go to so they can enjoy the NFL while they're there.<|endoftext|>
